# Allowlist .dockerignore — repo has 12 GB+ of circuit artifacts +
# Playwright fixtures + node_modules trees that the SPA build doesn't
# need. Naive denylist patterns missed enough that build context
# uploads ran past 500 MB before timeout. Allowlist is bulletproof:
# ignore everything, then re-include only what the Dockerfiles COPY.

# Step 1: ignore EVERYTHING
**

# Step 2: re-include only the packages + workspace files needed for
# the SPA build. Order: re-include the dirs before the files, then
# selectively include subtrees within them.

# Workspace root — we only need these specific files at the top level.
!package.json
!pnpm-workspace.yaml
!pnpm-lock.yaml
# tsconfig.base.json — extended by packages/sdk/tsconfig.build.json
# (and several other workspaces). Without it, tsc falls back to the
# default `target` (ES3), which trips BigInt-literal errors all over
# the SDK source.
!tsconfig*.json

# Web package — the SPA itself, plus all build-time inputs.
!packages
!packages/web
!packages/web/**

# SDK + contracts-sdk — workspace-aliased imports from web.
!packages/sdk
!packages/sdk/**
!packages/contracts-sdk
!packages/contracts-sdk/**

# Fixtures — qtspIndexPlugin reads fixtures/trust/*/*/meta.json at
# build start to emit src/generated/qtsp-index.ts. Without these the
# vite plugin throws.
!fixtures
!fixtures/trust
!fixtures/trust/**

# Deploy configs (the Dockerfile copies its own nginx.conf at build).
!deploy
!deploy/**

# Step 3: re-exclude the heavy bits that snuck in via the wide
# packages/web/** include. These are Playwright fixtures, build
# caches, and node_modules trees — none needed for `pnpm -F @zkqes/
# web build` from a clean slate (pnpm install rehydrates).
packages/web/node_modules/
packages/web/dist/
packages/web/tests/e2e/.r2-cache/
packages/web/tests/test-results/
packages/web/playwright-report/
packages/web/screenshots/
packages/web/.playwright-mcp/
packages/sdk/node_modules/
packages/sdk/dist/
packages/contracts-sdk/node_modules/
packages/contracts-sdk/dist/

# Top-level node_modules — pnpm-store is recreated by `pnpm install`.
node_modules/

# Belt-and-braces patterns matching what naive .dockerignore would
# ignore — anchor with **/ so they hit at any depth.
**/node_modules/
**/.pnpm-store/
**/dist/
!packages/web/tests/build/
!packages/web/tests/build/**
**/build/
**/out/
**/.turbo/
**/.cache/
**/coverage/
**/*.zkey
**/*.r1cs
**/*.wasm
**/*.sym
**/*.ptau
**/*.p7s
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
